# Environment and imports (Pulse UI)

## Environment variables

Use **`REACT_APP_`** prefix for client-exposed env vars. See `.env.example`. Examples: `REACT_APP_PULSE_SERVER_URL`, `REACT_APP_MOCK_API`. Access via `process.env.REACT_APP_*`. Don't commit secrets; document needed vars in `.env.example`.

## Import order (recommended)

1. React
2. Third-party (TanStack Query, React Router, Mantine, etc.)
3. Internal services / clients
4. Hooks (shared then feature)
5. Components
6. Types (`import type ...`)
7. Constants / utils
8. Styles (`import styles from './X.module.css'`)

Keep imports grouped and avoid circular dependencies. Prefer feature-local imports over deep `~/` paths when the file is in the same feature.
